## About

From website:

> Since our inception in 1991 we have expanded our compound collection by adding compounds from uncommon chemical classes which feature drug-like physico-chemical properties. Our libraries have been attractive to pharma, biotech and agrochemical companies around the world and now our in house stock exceeds 1 million unique compounds.

[Databases](http://www.enamine.net/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=94) include:

 * Building Blocks
 * Product Focus
 * Screening Collection
 * Libraries for Fragment-Based Drug Discovery
 * Drug-like Collection
 * Pre-plated representative sets
 * Carboxylic Acids Collection
 * Ligand-Based Approach Targeted Libraries
 * Receptor-Based Approach Targeted Libraries
 * 3-D Searching (Sybyl/Unity) Targeted Libraries
 * Agro-Like Targeted Libraries

## Downloading

Downloading databases requires [registration](http://www.enamine.net/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=19). 

## Openness

Not clear whether data is free for re-use or re-distribution.
